To authenticate with the Systeme.io Public API, you must use a public API key generated within your account's profile settings under the Public API keys section [1][2]. Include this key in every request by adding it to the X-API-Key HTTP header [3][2].

Example using JavaScript:

```javascript
fetch('https://api.systeme.io/api/contacts', {
    headers: {
        'X-API-Key': 'your_api_key'
    }
})
.then(response => response.json())
.then(data => console.log(data))
.catch(error => console.error('Error:', error));
```

The key can only be copied immediately after creation; if you lose it, you must delete it and generate a new one [4][3].
